{{Quote|You will return in triumph! A hero of the Republic! The illustrious Lorca Oviedo&mdash;Director General of the Oviedo Engineering dynasty.|[[Wat Tambor/Legends|Wat Tambor]], to Director General Lorca Oviedo|<ref name="Tales" />}}
'''Director General''' was a title used by [[Oviedo Engineering]],<ref name="Tales" /> a corporation that manufactured military equipment.<ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|II|432|Oviedo Engineering}}</ref> Around [[21 BBY/Legends|21 BBY]],<ref name="Date">{{Tales|22|Honor Bound}} is set approximately a [[Standard year/Legends|year]] after the events of {{Film|II}} and therefore around [[21 BBY/Legends|21 BBY]] per ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''.</ref> [[Lorca Oviedo]], the [[Director/Legends|director]]<ref name="CSWE" /> of Oviedo Engineering and a member of the<ref name="Tales" /> [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]],<ref name="CIS">{{DB|organization|cis|Confederacy of Independent Systems}}</ref> held the title. After [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] [[Clone commando/Legends|clone commandos]] [[Action on Asturias|discovered]] Oviedo's allegiance to the Confederacy on the<ref name="Tales" /> [[Expansion Region/Legends|Expansion Region]]<ref name="EAOC-Asturias">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-the-essential-atlas-online-companion|text=''Star Wars: The Essential Atlas'' Online Companion|int=Star Wars: The Essential Atlas Online Companion}} &mdash; Based on corresponding data for [[Asturias system/Legends|Asturias system]]</ref> [[Moon/Legends|moon]] [[Asturias]], they brought him to the Republic's<ref name="Tales" /> [[Core Worlds/Legends|Core Worlds]]<ref name="EAOC-Coruscant">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-the-essential-atlas-online-companion|text=''Star Wars: The Essential Atlas'' Online Companion|int=Star Wars: The Essential Atlas Online Companion}} &mdash; Based on corresponding data for [[Coruscant system]]</ref> [[Capital/Legends|capital]] [[Planet/Legends|planet]]<ref name="Coruscant">{{DB|location|coruscant|Coruscant}}</ref> [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] for questioning, where he [[Death/Legends|died]] of respiratory failure.<ref name="Tales" />

==Behind the scenes==
The title of Director General appeared in the flashbacks of the [[Star Wars comic books|comic]] story "[[Honor Bound]]," which was published by [[Dark Horse Comics]]<ref name="Tales" /> on [[February 23]], [[2005]]<ref name="Marvel">{{Marvel|url=comics/issue/54000/star_wars_tales_1999_22|text=Star Wars Tales (1999) #22}}</ref> as part of the [[Star Wars Tales 22|twenty-second]] issue of the ''[[Star Wars Tales]]'' comic-book series. The story was written by [[Ian Edginton]] and illustrated by [[Steve Pugh]].<ref name="Tales" /> In the real world, a Director General is the chief executive or administrator of an organization.<ref name="Dict">{{WebCite|url=https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/director_general|text=Director general Definition & Meaning|work=[[Wikipedia:Merriam-Webster|Merriam-Webster]]|archivedate=20220705044708}}</ref>

